emfmodeldistance

Class EcoreShortestPaths

  • java.lang.Object
    • emfmodeldistance.EcoreShortestPaths

  • public class EcoreShortestPaths
extends java.lang.Object
    This class allows to compute the shortests number of links from an EObject to another, given an ordered list of EObject from an Ecore model. It implements the Floyd-Warshall all paths shortest path algorithm. It computes the shortest path from any node to any node in O(|nodes|^3) time.
    Author:
    Eugene Syriani
    See Also:
    Wikipedia

      • EcoreShortestPaths

        public EcoreShortestPaths(java.util.List<org.eclipse.emf.ecore.EObject> nodes,
                          IEReferenceNavigator ref_nav)
        Implements the Floyd-Warshall all paths shortest path algorithm. It computes the shortest path from any node to any node in O(|nodes|^3) time.
        Parameters:
        nodes - sequence of nodes in the order they will be indexed in the resulting matrix
        ref_nav - interface to access the neighbors of each node

      • getAllPaths

        public int[][] getAllPaths()
        Returns the matrix of all paths from any source node to any target node. i and j indices are in the order provided by the original sequence of nodes.
        Returns:
        the matrix where (i,j)=k where k is the node that connects i to j
